      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a driver-focused example featuring the legendary S54B32 inline-six engine, characterized by its 8,000 RPM redline and individual throttle bodies. The powertrain is mated to a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission, delivering torque through a factory variable M differential lock. Critical preventative maintenance has been executed, including a comprehensive VANOS system overhaul and structural reinforcement of the rear subframe. The chassis retains its signature poise with a well-sorted MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension setup. While the exterior shows minor patina consistent with spirited use, the mechanical vitals remain sharp, offering the precise turn-in and linear power delivery synonymous with the M division\u2019s peak naturally aspirated era.",
